   <head>Song I</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|--+|--+|--+|-" line_length="12">'Midst beauty and pleasure's gay triumphs, to languish</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|--+|--+|--+|-" line_length="12">And droop without knowing the source of my anguish;</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|--+|--+|--+|-" line_length="12">To start from short slumbers and look for the morning â€”</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|--+|--+|--+|-" line_length="12">Yet close my dull eyes when I see it returning;</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|--+|--+|--+|-" line_length="12">Sighs sudden and frequent, looks ever dejected,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|--+|--+|--+|-" line_length="12">Sounds that steal from my tongue, by no meaning connected!</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|--+|--+|--+|-" line_length="12">Ah say, fellow-swains, how these symptoms befell me?</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|--+|--+|--+|-" line_length="12">They smile, but reply not. Sure Delia will tell me!</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
